<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900607-0024</DOCNO><DOCID>900607-0024.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Tambrands Inc.:   Relocation of Headquarters   Set in Plan to Cut Costs</HL><DATE>06/07/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   TMB</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><LP>   Tambrands Inc., a women's care products maker based inLake Success, N.Y., plans to move its headquarters toWestchester County, north of New York City, to cut costs bychoosing a smaller site.   The company said it will sell its Long Island offices andexpects to complete the move by the end of 1991. The new headoffice site, which hasn't been determined, will be closer toTambrands' Technical Center in Palmer, Mass., and to its U.S.plants, all in New York state or New England, which have atotal of 1,300 employees. Of the 200 employees in LakeSuccess, 50 will be offered posts at the Technical Center,which has 210 employees, and 150 will move to Westchester.Tambrands has 4,100 employees world-wide.</LP><TEXT>   In the past year, the company has determined to focus onfeminine care, with its Tampax tampons and Maxithins sanitarypads. Tambrands has been praised by analysts for its strongrestructuring moves, including payroll cuts and stockbuy-backs.</TEXT></DOC>